node.text:
THE TRUTH:

this photo was taken when i was really, really, really, happy. 

...and right now, i am struggling. and tbh i don’t feel like being a really, really, really, happy girl. 

and that’s okay. 

but, i know that this hard time will pass (2 Corinthians 4: 17-18) and i know that i will get better. but, i want you guys to know that i am no longer going to paint my life as “perfect” on social media. 

do you know how my social media got started? my story times. i want to be honest and real with you guys. and this is it— 

I used to film myself talking to my camera all the time. I got in the habit of recording myself whenever I was upset, hurt, or angry. Then, I’d turn the camera off, and forget about it. After I thought about it, I would replay the video, and write down WHY I was upset in the video. Then, I would write down what I learned from that situation. And lastly, I would figure out how I could make the situation funny. 

This is my thought process: 
Pain, Time, Question, Learn, Laugh about it. 

I have been doing this since I was 14 years old. So now, instead of going through that ENTIRE thought process every time— when something goes wrong in my life, I instantly think “How can I learn & make this funny?” And THAT is how my content is created. 

My “story times” on tiktok & YouTube, is how I cope. This is the process in which I get over things. 

But right now, I am hurting. And I’m finding it a little harder to go through this process by myself. I know that I’m going to understand the lesson from this time in my life eventually, but right now I am in the “Time” portion of my thought process. 

Social media is hard whenever you’re acting like you’re fine all the time. I apologize for not being real with you guys. I want to be real with you guys from here on out. I’m going to share my hurt, because I know that someone else can learn from it. 

Thank you guys for supporting me.
